00:26:58,572 --> 00:27:02,033
Those are all facets of the empathy exposed here.

451
00:27:03,620 --> 00:27:10,303
What I would ask you is if in the future you are thinking of fostering empathy for strangers,

452
00:27:10,303 --> 00:27:18,786
so actually using empathy in a multiplayer context, because of course saving the world

453
00:27:18,786 --> 00:27:21,608
or impacting the world starts in oneself.

454
00:27:21,608 --> 00:27:26,430
You have to empathize with yourself, you have to love yourself before you can love others.

455
00:27:26,430 --> 00:27:33,313
But a deeper change in the world is born from empathy with strangers in general.

456
00:27:34,794 --> 00:27:41,540
So I wonder if you could elaborate on this and if this is something on your mind.

457
00:27:41,540 --> 00:27:51,468
Do you want me to repeat the question? Or actually, I'll just say this.

458
00:27:51,468 --> 00:27:58,374
Yes, it's true to say that this game is very much about building empathy for yourself and those close to you.

459
00:28:00,018 --> 00:28:07,243
And if there was one thing that I could like add to it and improve on it, it would be just that,

460
00:28:07,243 --> 00:28:15,949
to expand that circle and to include more people in that feeling of empathy, to make sure that,

461
00:28:15,949 --> 00:28:28,137
you know, build solidarity, build, you know, teach people to be nice, teach people to be inclusive.

462
00:28:28,137 --> 00:28:28,918
So yes, I would do exactly that.

463
00:28:29,480 --> 00:28:30,801
Thank you.

464
00:28:30,801 --> 00:28:31,441
Okay, thank you.

465
00:28:31,441 --> 00:28:32,542
This looks like a stunning game, I have to say.

466
00:28:32,542 --> 00:28:36,865
I can imagine this could be very good for developing empathy for young children.

